Compound nesting: sibling transition within a region, then an absolute
transition that exits the region into a top-level final state.
-- machine.json --
{
  "id": "h",
  "initial": "a",
  "states": {
    "a": {
      "initial": "a1",
      "states": {
        "a1": { "on": { "E": { "target": "a2" } } },
        "a2": { "on": { "UP": { "target": "#b" } } }
      }
    },
    "b": { "type": "final" }
  }
}
-- scenario --
expect active a.a1
send E
expect active a.a2
send UP
expect active b
expect status done
